BRIEFING:
STRONG SURFACE HIGH PRESSURE NORTH OF THE STATE WILL GRADUALLY PROGRESS EASTWARD OVER THE NEXT SEVERAL DAYS AND BRING BREEZY TO LOCALLY WINDY TRADE WINDS TO THE MAIN HAWAIIAN ISLANDS. THESE WINDS WILL LIKELY GENERATE LOW-LEVEL TURBULENCE LEE OF MOUNTAIN TERRAIN, SEE AIRMET TANGO FOR DETAILS. PERIODS OF CLOUDS AND BRIEF SHOWERS WILL FAVOR WINDWARD AND MAUKA AREAS, PARTICULARLY DURING THE OVERNIGHT TO EARLY MORNING HOURS. BRIEF MVFR CEILINGS AND VISIBILITY WILL BE POSSIBLE IN SHOWERS. OTHERWISE, VFR CONDITIONS WILL PREVAIL.
THREAT: NO SIGMETS IN AREA OF OPERATION.
